description:
Whenever I talk about Mr. Holmes Bakeshop, I'm always reminded of Sherlock Holmes. It's quite an interesting visualization actually. I imagine Benedict Cumberbatch wearing a chef's hat, his right hand raised in a peace sign, serving some pastries. Yeah, I have the funniest thoughts sometimes. Anyway, here are some useful tips:

1) The bakery begins serving cruffins at 9am, and they usually sell out by 11am. I would advise arriving at 8:45am. If you come too late, the line extends out the door and up the block.
2) You can only order up to 2 cruffins per person. Babies count; dogs don't. Although I'd like to think the hound of the Baskervilles would totally count if it were real.
3) Only 1 type of cruffin is sold per day. There is no "regular" flavor. Check Instagram for their flavors on each day of the week. https://www.instagram.com/mrholmesbakehouse/
4) You need to order at least 6 pastries to get the pretty box. Otherwise, it costs a little extra.
5) Take photos. Lots of them. Everything about this bakery is so picturesque - the pastries, the boxes, and of course the iconic neon-lit sign.

// Cruffin, Salted Dark Chocolate Pumpkin ($4.50) - 5 stars
// Donut, Coconut Blood Orange ($3.50) - 5 stars
// Strawberry Jalapeño Bearclaw ($4.50) - 4 stars
// Churro Croissant ($4.00) - 4 stars
// Plain Croissant ($3.50) - 3 stars

I've been waiting to come here for so long and finally I was here on a weekday (i hear that the weekend lines are CRAZY) and o was up early in the morning.

I got there at about 8:30 on a Thursday and was the fourth person in line. I didn't want to take a chance and miss it! They only serve a certain number of cruffins a day and each person is limited to two cruffins each. today's special was mocha cruffin with cocoa nibs. YUM! Be prepared to pay about $4 a cruffin...and $1.50 for an adorable white and gold box if you're kinda weird like me.

They've also got other bakery items such as croissants and pastries as well! But let's be real...you come for the cruffins and get pastry items for your friends (;
